analysis: The documents primarily concern the management, reservation, withdrawal, and restoration of public lands in California. They frequently reference the act of June 25, 1910, as amended, which authorizes the President to make withdrawals of public lands. The documents address various purposes for these land actions, including protecting hot springs, creating national monuments, establishing lookout stations for forest protection, Indian use, reclamation projects, and pending land resurveys. Some orders revoke or modify previous executive orders related to land management.
title: California Land Management and Resource Allocation
